column1: NOTE:  Columns 2-5 below contain the following output data
Column 2:   conditional probabilities P(at least one bank from G1 going default|all banks in G2 default)
Column 3:   conditional probabilities P(at least one bank from G2 going default|all banks in G1 default)
Column 4:   conditional probabilities P(all banks in G1 going default|all banks in G2 default)
Column 5:   conditional probabilities P(all banks in G2 going default|all banks in G1 default)
where G1 is quadGroup1 defined in the setting file and G2 consists of all the banks not in G1. In this case

column2: P(at least one from G1 going default|G2 default)
column3: P(at least one from G2 going default|G1 default)
